312
00:12:22,868 --> 00:12:26,871
...not a hotel, so when you
walk inside, it's personal.

313
00:12:26,913 --> 00:12:28,789
Once obsessed with
nothing but working

314
00:12:28,831 --> 00:12:31,522
the hardest, the
longest, being the best,

315
00:12:31,523 --> 00:12:33,878
Marco has transferred
his obsessive nature

316
00:12:33,920 --> 00:12:37,173
to the more pleasurable task
of making the Rudloe Arms

317
00:12:37,174 --> 00:12:38,883
his perfect place.

318
00:12:38,925 --> 00:12:41,802
What's important
about a restaurant

319
00:12:41,844 --> 00:12:44,723
is the feel, not a look.

320
00:12:44,763 --> 00:12:47,726
You could go to the best
restaurant in the world tomorrow.

321
00:12:47,766 --> 00:12:48,928
They could serve the best food.

322
00:12:48,935 --> 00:12:51,812
But if you don't feel comfortable
within that environment,

323
00:12:51,854 --> 00:12:53,314
you'll never enjoy it.

324
00:12:53,356 --> 00:12:58,528
Inside is as much a project
as the grounds, every detail.

325
00:12:58,570 --> 00:13:01,656
Then you can be yourself.

326
00:13:01,698 --> 00:13:03,324
Number one, environment.

327
00:13:03,366 --> 00:13:04,825
Number two, service.

328
00:13:04,867 --> 00:13:06,369
Number three, food.

329
00:13:08,162 --> 00:13:12,125
A pan-roasted filet of
beef with escargot.

330
00:13:12,166 --> 00:13:15,336
Whoa. It's beautiful.

331
00:13:15,378 --> 00:13:16,837
Who do you want to come here?

332
00:13:16,879 --> 00:13:18,715
People who enjoy themselves.

333
00:13:18,757 --> 00:13:19,840
I like a mixed demographic.

334
00:13:19,882 --> 00:13:21,301
- I wanna have everybody.
- Uh-hmm.

335
00:13:21,342 --> 00:13:23,844
I don't want to just
target one market.

336
00:13:23,886 --> 00:13:25,930
Food should be affordable.

337
00:13:28,767 --> 00:13:30,101
Very, very good.

338
00:13:30,143 --> 00:13:33,730
Has your food always reflected
your aspirations and dreams

339
00:13:33,772 --> 00:13:35,148
rather than where you came from?

340
00:13:35,189 --> 00:13:38,234
I was born and bred on the
outskirts of Leeds in a project

341
00:13:38,235 --> 00:13:38,859
housing estate.

342
00:13:38,901 --> 00:13:41,780
Even though I was born into
very humble beginnings,

343
00:13:41,820 --> 00:13:44,865
I used to cross my road,
walk over the golf course,

344
00:13:44,907 --> 00:13:47,744
and there I was on the
Harewood Estates,

345
00:13:47,786 --> 00:13:51,018
designed by the great Capability
Brown, the stately home

346
00:13:51,019 --> 00:13:52,123
of the Earl of Harewood.

347
00:13:52,165 --> 00:13:54,083
That was my playground.

348
00:13:55,585 --> 00:13:58,505
I was fascinated by
the countryside.

349
00:13:58,546 --> 00:14:01,362
I loved the rivers, the
streams, the brooks,

350
00:14:01,363 --> 00:14:02,300
the fields, the woods.

351
00:14:02,342 --> 00:14:06,721
What was within them,
that's what captured me.

352
00:14:06,763 --> 00:14:08,765
It was a dream.

353
00:14:08,807 --> 00:14:11,892
That was my escapism.

354
00:14:11,934 --> 00:14:13,186
My mother died when I was six.

355
00:14:13,227 --> 00:14:16,731
Mother Nature, she became
my surrogate mother.

356
00:14:16,773 --> 00:14:18,899
And so, therefore, I
have this amazing

357
00:14:18,941 --> 00:14:22,320
love affair with nature.

358
00:14:22,362 --> 00:14:24,322
But look, once you go into
a high-end restaurant,

359
00:14:24,364 --> 00:14:27,429
you're about as far as
from nature as you can be.

360
00:14:27,430 --> 00:14:29,910
I mean, it's hard to
rise up the ranks

361
00:14:29,952 --> 00:14:32,914
